== English ==
=== Etymology ===

From [[wikipedia:Kannada|Kannada]] '''Bengaluru'''. The source of the name Bengaluru is usually attributed to ''Benga-val-ooru'' (City of Guards) in Old Kannada or ''Benda-kaal-ooru'' (Town of Boiled Beans) from Kannada folklore. 
